title: Whirlpool Tops Earnings Expectations, Despite Currency Hit
text:
Whirlpool Corp., the worldâ€™s largest home-appliance manufacturer by sales, beat earnings expectations in its latest quarter, thanks to cost cuts and acquisitions that drove European and Asian sales.
The company reported a profit of $235 million, or $2.95 a share, up from year-earlier earnings of $230 million, or $2.88 a share. Whirlpool said earnings from ongoing operations rose to $3.45 a share, well above the $3.29 analysts...
